## Scripts

Scripts in `agent/scripts/src/` support this workflow. A Python venv is pre-configured
at `agent/scripts/.venv/` with all dependencies installed.

{{SCRIPTS_LIST}}
<!-- List each script with a one-line description. Example:
     - `gen_html.py` -- Generates HTML reports from analysis data.
     - `fetch_data.py` -- Fetches records from the project API.
     If no workflow-specific scripts, write: "Built-in export scripts only (gen_document.py, gen_xlsx.py)." -->

To run a script:
```bash
source agent/scripts/.venv/bin/activate
python agent/scripts/src/{script_name}.py
```

To run tests:
```bash
source agent/scripts/.venv/bin/activate
python -m pytest agent/scripts/tests/
```

To add a new script after initial generation, use `add_script()` from
`forge/scripts/src/scaffold.py`, then call `install_dependencies()` to
install any new pip packages into the venv.

